# Image Cache Directory

This directory stores locally cached card images as a fallback tier in the multi-source image loading chain.

## Structure
```
/images/
  ├── cards/           # Individual card images (PNG format)
  │   └── [card-name-slug].png
  └── .htaccess        # Apache config for serving images
```

## Fallback Chain
1. Scryfall API (format=image) - Primary
2. Scryfall normal format - Secondary  
3. Scryfall border-cropped - Tertiary
4. Cardmarket proxy - Quaternary
5. **Local cache** (`/images/cards/[name].png`) - Final fallback before placeholder

## Populating Cache
Run `download_card_images.py` to extract unique card names from HTML and download images:
```bash
python download_card_images.py
```

This will create PNG files named with URL-safe slugs (e.g., "ajanis-response.png").